Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Lightly oil a #baking sheet{}. Wash and dry produce (except green beans). Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Toss on one side of prepared sheet with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, half the @Sweet and Smoky BBQ Seasoning{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step), @pepper{}, and a big pinch of @salt{}. (For 4, spread potatoes out across entire sheet.) Roast on top rack for ~{5%minutes} (you'll add the chicken then).

Meanwhile, place 1 TBSP @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a medium #microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until melted, about ~{30%seconds}. Stir in a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, remaining BBQ Seasoning, pepper, and a big pinch of salt. Add @Panko Breadcrumbs{½%cup} and stir until evenly combined.

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper. Evenly spread @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon} onto tops of chicken; mound with panko mixture, pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides). Once potatoes have roasted 5 minutes, remove #sheet{} from oven; carefully place coated chicken on empty side. (For 4 servings, leave potatoes roasting and add chicken to a second sheet.)

Roast chicken and potatoes on top rack until chicken is browned and cooked through and potatoes are crispy, ~{15-18%minutes}. (For 4 servings, roast chicken on middle rack.)

When chicken and potatoes are almost done, pierce @Green Beans{6%ounce} bag with a fork; place bag on a #plate{}. Microwave until tender, about ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If you like, toss green beans in a bowl with 1 TBSP butter.

Divide chicken, potatoes, and green beans between plates. Drizzle chicken with as much @Mike's Hot Honey®{¾%ounce} as you like and serve.